sense.def:
To fill a container or area
pomeni dati veliko količino nečesa v posodo ali območje, tako da je polno.

seg.quote: Fill the teapot with boiling water.

sense.def:
Kadar nekaj
fills a space
, je tako veliko, da poleg ostane zelo malo prostora.

seg.quote: ...a large hall filled with rows of desks.

sense.def:
To fill
pomeni postati poln predmetov, oseb ali snovi.

Kadar nekaj
fills someone with an emotion
ali kadar čustvo
fills someone
, nekdo močno občuti tisto čustvo.

seg.quote: His son's lies filled him with anger.

sense.def:
Kadar neka dejavnost ali obstoj nečesa
fills a need or gap
, zadovolji potrebo ali zapolni praznino.

seg.quote: The Alliance filled the political vacuum.

sense.def:
Kadar nekaj
fills a role or position
, opravlja določeno nalogo ali ima poseben prostor v nekem sistemu.

seg.quote: It has filled this role in a most satisfactory way for many years.

sense.def:
To have had one's fill of something
pomeni ne želeti si, da bi nekaj spet doživeli ali storili.

To fill in a form
pomeni zapisati podatke v temu namenjene prostorčke na obrazcu.

seg.quote: Fill in your name and address.

sense.def:
To fill someone in
pomeni nekomu dati podrobne podatke o nečem.

seg.quote: I'll fill you in on the details now.

sense.def:
To fill in for someone else
pomeni opravljati delo nekoga drugega med njegovo odsotnostjo.

To fill out a form
pomeni zapisati podatke v temu namenjene prostorčke na obrazcu.

seg.quote: I've filled out the death certificate.

sense.def:
Kadar vitek človek
fills out
, postane obilnejši.

To fill up a container
pomeni dati večjo količino nečesa v posodo, tako da je polna.

seg.quote: Fill up his seed bowl twice a day.

sense.def:
Kadar neki prostor
fills up
, ga stvari ali ljudje napolnijo.

seg.quote: His office began to fill up with people.
